="https://i.imgur.com/BITtAco.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/FTZVsXd</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[TheQueenOfEverything]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>there is something strange at this exit</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/tavuhya</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eVLQBG8.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/tavuhya</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[smartguy1337]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>“If they can't abide by the rules and laws how can they rule over our laws”</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ZwvoTvD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Hwl70zw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://twitter.com/itsjefftiedrich/status/1522240234200649729?s=21&t=igXe3OiNos4GyMBWuG98RA</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ZwvoTvD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[reservatio]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Dibs on the black knight with the mace</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/upGdnkz</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AK2uMOk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#nostalgia</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/upGdnkz</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GrandChampion]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Mama's good boi :)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/1SovCoW</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/s8DfM7o.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Source : https://instagram.com/ms_nadineslife</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/1SovCoW</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Rammsteinstochter]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Some wounds can't heal</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XND75PZ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/571AOJn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is Elizabeth, my fiance (on the right) and I 

She passed away last August of a sudden heart attack.  She was only 31.  I found her in bed some point shortly after the heart attack. She was still warm when I realized that she needed help.  I tried my very, very best to do CPR and bring her back, I tried so hard. I begged her not to die and I begged her not to leave me,  but she was too far gone, according to the paramedic I spoke with that night.  It's been almost eight or nine months since then, not sure which. I can't be bothered to even do the math.  I'm not posting here for a pity party, or because I want to hurt myself or anything like that. I'm posting here because I learned the ultimate lesson that life and love has to teach you that night, and I just wish I could go back in time and tell myself to cherish the gifts that God had given me.  I wish I could go back and cherish my best friend.  If I could I would go back and spoil her every day of her life until she got sick of it, lol.  I would go back and take back all the arguments that seem so incredibly trivial now.  I wish I could go back and just hold her one last time, really tell her how much I loved her and how much everyone around her loved her and how much of a difference she had made.  

And how she left behind a bottomless pit of grief. The price we all have to pay when we really love someone, then lose them.  It's been eight or nine months since I lost my fiance, but more importantly my best friend, and the kindest person I have ever come across. And it seems like yesterday, folks. The pain doesn't go away, and the tears turn into a friendly reminder of how important this person was to you.  How your pain and grief is just a testament to the love you shared with this person. Those wounds don't truly heal, but they become easier to manage.  

I spend my time, during this stage of my life, desperately trying to find reason in passages I read. Really trying to find someone or something that could truly paint a picture of the misery you experience when you lose someone you never dreamed of living without.   I haven't been able to find anything, so it just seemed appropriate to make my own post.  At least one of you knows this feeling, and I hope you know that you're not alone. It may seem like no one understands, but don't hold that against them. Don't give up.

Not sure if anyone has even bothered to read this far, but I wrote a poem that I would like to share with Beth, and this seems as appropriate a spot as any. 

Beth
Once, I said,
Like people often do,
That you were my exception.
That you made everything shitty about the world into beauty.
And I believed it.
It was the truth.
I put my faith in you. 
All my faith in the universe, I put into you.
Everything works out in the end, and you were living proof.
And then you weren't.
You were gone.
And I knew it.
I knew I wouldn't be able to find you.
But I looked anyway.
I knew better, and still I look for you.
Time has passed since we lost you.
And I should definitely know better now.
But I keep looking.
Surely, you can't really be gone.
Surely, this has to be a nightmare.
Too many people need you.
Too much shared love, lost instead.
The hearts you touched. 
The lives you breathed life back into.
They weep. 
They're confused.
They needed that love.
You're gone now, but
now and then...
I will catch a light at the edge of my vision.
A spectre of you, dancing in the corner of my eyes.
Small, subtle signs that
you're still here. 
You still love us.
You're sorry you had to leave.
So I have to keep looking.
In spite of knowing better.
Because I know,
there's no way you're really gone.
We buried you. 
I held your hand.
I kissed you, one last time.
And we gave you back to the earth.
But I feel you, alive, in my heart.
I see you, so often now, dancing in the corner of my vision.
You will never be truly gone from us. 
I won't stop looking until I find you.
I miss you, Baby.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/M8oQpMC.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Anyone reading this, grab someone you love, someone that you don't think you could ever live without. Tell them you love them. Tell them they're your entire world. Hug the shit out of them. Make exceptions for them.  Don't ever leave anything unsaid, because we really don't know when our time will come to an end, and you don't need to live with those regrets. Love is always the answer.  I miss you, Beth. I love you to the moon and back!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XND75PZ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[samuelthastings5]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Congrats!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/vMHqKl3</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/93JHBud.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://www.facebook.com/photo/?fbid=401953635369550&set=a.201905705374345</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/vMHqKl3</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[LetsGoBidenFckOffBrandon]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NTwsxVC</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TKIqTcp.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NTwsxVC</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ihaveaverybadfeelingaboutthis]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Red hair</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/cz2dCAq</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AOtaO4k.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I have red hair now so here’s a doodle of myself https://www.patreon.com/miaormoa</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/cz2dCAq</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[miaormoa]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Time to get civilized.</title><link>https://imgur.com/